Hi Nancy: 




It was great to speak with you today. 




I prepared a letter that summarizes what we hope to do. 




On behalf of the Fraser Valley Croquet Society, I am writing to express our interest in the property at 7560 Hurd, the former Mission Lawn Bowling Society site. Our society hopes to have some access to the former lawn bowling court for playing and teaching croquet. The location could serve as a hub for learners of all ages, collaborating with local organizations like the Leisure Centre. We would work with the Mission Arts Council to resolve insurance, scheduling and maintenance issues. The society will offer training programs for new players and even organize small tournaments, providing a unique recreational option for Mission residents, bringing people together and promoting physical activity. 




We are excited about the potential of this property and believe that our proposed croquet teaching effort aligns well with the city's vision of promoting sports and community engagement. 

The Fraser Valley Croquet Society has also been working with the Abbotsford Lawn Bowling Club to add croquet as a sporting option. The plan has been popular, with several players turning out for demonstration events. 




Thank you for considering our proposal. We look forward to a fruitful collaboration that benefits 

our society members, the Mission Arts Council, and the city of Mission. 




Sincerely, 

Michael Kernaghan 

Director, Fraser Valley Croquet Society 

